Q: Laravel and PHP?
Laravel is a framework for PHP 5+

Q: PHP online Documentation ?
http://php.net/mcrypt-module-open

Q: PHP configuration file?
php --ini                                                   # <-- reread the configuration files
Configuration File (php.ini) Path: /etc/php5/cli            # <-- CLI = Command Line Interface
Loaded Configuration File:         /etc/php5/cli/php.ini
Scan for additional .ini files in: /etc/php5/cli/conf.d
Additional .ini files parsed:      /etc/php5/cli/conf.d/pdo.ini

Q: How many version of PHP are installed?
$ sudo updatedb
$ locate --regex .*/php$
/etc/alternatives/php
/usr/bin/php
/var/lib/dpkg/alternatives/php

Q: What are PHAR files?
PHAR files are PHP archives
Composer.phar can be executed as 
php composer.phar
or
mv composer.phar composer
./composer

Q: Which PHP modules are installed?
* From a terminal: php -m (or php -i)
* From a index.php
cat > /var/www/index.php <<EOT
<?php

print_r (phpinfo());

?>
EOT
!!! In the latter case, installed modules and their configurations are listed after the HTTP Headers Information section

Q: Laravel requires the Mcrypt PHP extension. ?
Mcrypt php module is not installed !
Modules are configured in php.ini
php -v
php --ini
php -i | grep "mcrypt support"


